data.description: Located in fun-loving Neighborhood 13, where hosting Mardi Gras is a yearly event, this choice Sun City Texas LaSalle is also on a pretty corner lot, where a large stone Patio extends the outdoor living area.  Evergreen landscaping welcomes you to this one-owner home, where a Front Sitting Porch is a feature not seen on every home of this plan.  Inside, crown molding and trim molding defines the Foyer, off of which resides the Dining Room and nearby Butler's Pantry, ideal for Texas-sized entertaining.  Ahead, tile floors blanket the sizable Great Room, where abundant wall space makes way for your flat-screen.  Open to the Great Room, the Island Kitchen hosts stainless-steel appliances and a Menu Desk, a perfect place to park the devices.  Adjacent, a roomy bayed Breakfast Room views the landscaped back yard.  Off the Kitchen is the before-mentioned Butler's Pantry and a superb Laundry, where custom cabinets bestow a wide folding area, or Coffee Bar.  Well-placed, the adjoining Extended Two-Car Garage makes bringing-in groceries a breeze.  Meanwhile, twin sets of full-view glass doors in the Great Room open onto the large stone Patio with its outdoor living possibilities.  At the rear of the home, yet another bay window enlarges the Primary Bedroom, while a spacious Walk-In Closet is very accessible.  A soothing jetted tub enhances the Primary Bath, where a roomy shower and dual vanities complete the suite.  Across the home, Two Guest Bedrooms are each accessible to the Guest Bath with shower, an upgrade, when this home was built.  There, a high transom window provides rich natural lighting.   Near softball and community gardening, this home is also handy to Highway 195 and its easy access to ABIA and Historical Downtown Georgetown.
